===Etymology 5===
Variant of {{m|en|roche|gloss=rock}}. Attested since the seventeenth century.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{senseid|en|stratum}}{{lb|en|UK|obsolete|mining}} A bed or stratum of some mineral.
#* {{quote-journal|year=1749|author=Rog. Mostyn|title=Mineralogy|work=Philosophical Transactions and Collections to the End of the Year|location=London|publisher=Royal Society|volume=II|oclc=149630598|page=379|passage=After long Working of this Coal, it was found upon the rising Grounds, that there lay another '''''Roach''''' of Coal, at the Depth of 14 Yards under it}}
# {{lb|en|UK|regional}} Gritty or coarse rock; ''especially'' [[Portland stone]] or similar [[limestone]].
#* {{quote-journal|year=1841|author=C.H. Smith|title=Lithology; or Observations on Stone for Building|work=The Surveyor, Engineer, and Architect|oclc=33911436|page=13|passage=The '''roach''', both of the top and bottom beds, is always imperceptibly incorporated with the freestone, which is invariable situated beneath it.}}

